<item>
            <title>[HBASE-9790] If MAX_FILESIZE is negative, cluster will split regions indefinitely</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-9790</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&apos;Alter&apos; was issued with wrong (negative) max_file_size. At some moment regionservers begin to split regions producing zero size regions. Table won&apos;t to delete, even can&apos;t disable it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Solution: stop cluster, delete table from hdfs, use with care  &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;hbase org.apache.hadoop.hbase.util.hbck.OfflineMetaRepair&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;0.92.1-cdh4.1.1, Ubuntu 12.04&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
